    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Vegetable Pulav</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup basmati rice</li>
            <li>2 cups mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, beans), chopped</li>
            <li>1 large onion, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>1/4 cup cashews</li>
            <li>1/4 cup raisins</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons ghee or vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
            <li>1-inch cinnamon stick</li>
            <li>3-4 green cardamom pods</li>
            <li>5-6 cloves</li>
            <li>1 bay leaf</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>2 cups water</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>vegetarian</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Rinse the basmati rice under cold water until the water runs clear. Soak it in water for 30 minutes, then drain.</li>
            <li>In a large pot, heat ghee or vegetable oil over medium heat. Add cumin seeds, cinnamon stick, cardamom pods, cloves, and bay leaf. Sauté for a minute until the spices release their aroma.</li>
            <li>Add sliced onions and cook until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add cashews and raisins. Sauté until the cashews are lightly golden.</li>
            <li>Add mixed vegetables and sauté for 2-3 minutes until they are slightly tender.</li>
            <li>Add soaked and drained basmati rice. Stir well to coat the rice with the vegetables and spices.</li>
            <li>Add turmeric powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Pour in water and bring the mixture to a boil. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until the rice is cooked and the water is absorbed.</li>
            <li>Remove the pot from heat and let it sit, covered, for 5 minutes. Fluff the rice with a fork.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.</li>
            <li>Serve hot as a delightful Vegetable Pulav.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Vegetable Pulav!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
